cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with information theory and its application to multi-party scenarios. Specifically, it provides one-shot rate regions for distributed source coding and multiple-access channels. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves multiple parties, which suggests the categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with data compression, which falls under the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with non-asymptotic scenarios, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
